Citations
Date: 0/0/1953
Source: Musterer on Molesworth
Author: STRONACH
Vol / Page: 14
Edition:
Quote: Some of us had added to our boots what is known as a `counter'. It is a stiff piece of leather, which, commencing at the instep, runs round the back of the boot, above the heel proper, acts as an ankle support, and prevents its wearer from `going over'.
